00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:31,230 --> 00:01:35,979
[A Lonely Hero's Journey]

3
00:01:36,370 --> 00:01:38,870
[Episode 28]

4
00:02:00,420 --> 00:02:01,640
Huang Qiushou! Let go!

5
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:03,240
Let go of the steering wheel!

6
00:02:03,590 --> 00:02:05,070
Let go!

7
00:02:05,580 --> 00:02:06,270
Let go!

8
00:02:21,870 --> 00:02:22,870
Vice Director Gu!

9
00:02:27,310 --> 00:02:28,110
What's wrong?

10
00:02:32,980 --> 00:02:36,640
[Gu's Mansion]

11
00:02:38,230 --> 00:02:39,090
Captain Zhang,

12
00:02:40,250 --> 00:02:41,070
what's wrong?

13
00:02:41,220 --> 00:02:43,220
There's an urgent official matter.

14
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:45,430
What's so urgent that it can't wait until morning?

15
00:02:45,430 --> 00:02:47,360
We only get around a hundred legal tenders per month.

16
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:49,490
How can you order him around like this?

17
00:02:51,110 --> 00:02:53,390
Fine, I'll go with you.

18
00:02:54,430 --> 00:02:57,290
At least let him get changed before coming with you.

19
00:03:29,670 --> 00:03:30,900
Where is the man now?

20
00:03:31,220 --> 00:03:33,020
In the interrogation room, sir.

21
00:03:33,270 --> 00:03:34,329
He's already dead.

22
00:03:35,510 --> 00:03:37,910
Are you going to interrogate a dead person?

23
00:03:38,990 --> 00:03:39,790
I...

24
00:03:41,030 --> 00:03:42,829
don't know where to put him.

25
00:03:43,990 --> 00:03:45,150
I'm really sorry.

26
00:03:47,210 --> 00:03:48,550
How many of our men died?

27
00:03:49,710 --> 00:03:51,950
One. He was shot by accident.

28
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:05,510
Director, I've brought Gu Yizhong here.

29
00:04:05,670 --> 00:04:08,670
What's the damn use of bringing him here now?

30
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:10,570
Xie Wenchao,

31
00:04:10,950 --> 00:04:12,420
why are you snapping at me?

32
00:04:14,270 --> 00:04:14,950
Director,

33
00:04:16,940 --> 00:04:17,899
what happened?

34
00:04:20,950 --> 00:04:22,540
Huang is dead!

35
00:04:24,070 --> 00:04:25,990
We initially wanted Huang Qiushou

36
00:04:25,990 --> 00:04:27,320
to identify Gu Yizhong.

37
00:04:27,550 --> 00:04:29,150
Because of my negligence...

38
00:04:30,470 --> 00:04:31,250
Sir,

39
00:04:31,670 --> 00:04:34,830
how can we let a dead person

40
00:04:35,310 --> 00:04:36,510
identify Gu Yizhong?

41
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:44,409
Huang Qiushou couldn't identify Gu Yizhong,

42
00:04:45,310 --> 00:04:46,810
but we can have Gu Yizhong

43
00:04:46,840 --> 00:04:48,240
identify Huang Qiushou.

44
00:04:53,610 --> 00:04:56,130
[Build Our Country in Peace]

45
00:04:54,510 --> 00:04:55,710
Come identify a body.

46
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:03,950
Director.

47
00:06:04,150 --> 00:06:05,610
Do you recognize this man?

48
00:06:07,230 --> 00:06:07,870
No.

49
00:06:08,950 --> 00:06:11,590
Huang Zuchong, editor-in-charge of the architecture section

50
00:06:11,590 --> 00:06:14,910
of Shanghai Hwa Hsia Illustrated.

51
00:06:16,630 --> 00:06:18,870
His real name was Huang Qiushou,

52
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:22,230
a senior agent of the CPC in Jiangsu Province.

53
00:06:22,230 --> 00:06:23,160
He was an expert.

54
00:06:25,830 --> 00:06:26,590
What a pity.

55
00:06:29,430 --> 00:06:31,600
He died in a car accident.

56
00:06:34,270 --> 00:06:35,159
You really don't know him?

57
00:06:35,159 --> 00:06:35,909
No.

58
00:06:37,950 --> 00:06:38,830
I know him.

59
00:06:40,890 --> 00:06:44,530
[Build Our Country in Peace]

60
00:06:42,520 --> 00:06:43,970
Huang Qiushou and I

61
00:06:45,860 --> 00:06:47,510
went way back.

62
00:06:55,130 --> 00:06:58,190
Back then, I was in the Special Agent Section of the CPC.

63
00:06:58,720 --> 00:06:59,840
My office was

64
00:07:00,100 --> 00:07:01,460
two doors down from his.

65
00:07:03,420 --> 00:07:04,890
I still can't forget

66
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:07,940
that he liked noodles.

67
00:07:09,430 --> 00:07:10,890
He made homemade noodles.

68
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:15,060
The first bowl of handmade noodles in my life

69
00:07:15,980 --> 00:07:17,250
was made by him.

70
00:07:22,370 --> 00:07:24,170
He treated his colleagues well,

71
00:07:25,710 --> 00:07:27,370
and he had a good personality.

72
00:07:28,350 --> 00:07:30,030
He was sincere, kind,

73
00:07:31,390 --> 00:07:33,600
and gentle.

74
00:07:34,270 --> 00:07:36,310
He was also the strongest believer in communism

75
00:07:36,310 --> 00:07:39,310
I've ever seen.

76
00:07:41,830 --> 00:07:43,080
Huang Zuchong

77
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:44,700
was indeed admirable.

78
00:07:46,620 --> 00:07:48,620
Although we're on different sides,

79
00:07:51,190 --> 00:07:52,230
he was a good man.

80
00:07:56,620 --> 00:07:58,310
I only recently found out

81
00:07:58,540 --> 00:08:00,000
that he went back to Suzhou

82
00:08:00,890 --> 00:08:02,310
to develop downlines.

83
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:07,070
One of his downlines is Lonely Boat.

84
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:12,590
My hunch tells me that you're the Lonely Boat.

85
00:08:15,950 --> 00:08:16,590
Director,

86
00:08:16,970 --> 00:08:18,770
you can't joke about this.

87
00:08:22,230 --> 00:08:23,430
I have my reasons.

88
00:08:24,830 --> 00:08:25,390
First,

89
00:08:26,430 --> 00:08:28,990
both of you studied architecture.

90
00:08:29,830 --> 00:08:31,830
Second, both of you studied abroad.

91
00:08:32,549 --> 00:08:33,270
Third,

92
00:08:34,429 --> 00:08:37,440
you've been subscribing to Hwa Hsia Illustrated.

93
00:08:37,919 --> 00:08:40,390
Director, if I remember correctly,

94
00:08:40,659 --> 00:08:42,590
Hwa Hsia Illustrated

95
00:08:42,610 --> 00:08:44,490
sells 25,000 copies of each issue.

96
00:08:44,490 --> 00:08:45,990
I'm not the only subscriber

97
00:08:45,990 --> 00:08:47,520
at the No. 90 Agent Station.

98
00:08:47,590 --> 00:08:48,190
Also,

99
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:50,120
I remember that your wife is also

100
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:51,120
a subscriber.

101
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:53,100
You have been investigating me?

102
00:08:53,490 --> 00:08:54,260
It's okay.

103
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:57,200
I'll go home and investigate my wife.

104
00:08:58,380 --> 00:09:00,020
You're not his downline?

105
00:09:00,430 --> 00:09:01,290
I'm really not.

106
00:09:05,310 --> 00:09:07,430
Identify his wound for me.

107
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:08,120
Come on.

108
00:09:10,910 --> 00:09:12,450
See if he died

109
00:09:12,470 --> 00:09:14,200
from blood loss from the aorta.

110
00:09:26,390 --> 00:09:27,390
What do you think?

111
00:09:28,590 --> 00:09:29,230
Director,

112
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:31,220
I really don't know

113
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:33,130
about this.

114
00:09:47,130 --> 00:09:49,130
All right, I have no more questions.

115
00:09:50,730 --> 00:09:52,730
I'll leave if there's nothing else.

116
00:09:53,300 --> 00:09:54,230
If you want to

117
00:09:54,230 --> 00:09:56,190
know about Huang Qiushou one day,

118
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:57,620
you can come and ask me.

119
00:09:59,390 --> 00:10:01,070
I probably should be the person

120
00:10:01,070 --> 00:10:03,070
who knows him the best in this world.

121
00:10:05,810 --> 00:10:06,940
I'm not interested.

122
00:10:08,990 --> 00:10:10,900
Okay, goodbye, Mr. Lonely Boat.

123
00:10:22,550 --> 00:10:29,620
[Build Our Country in Peace]

124
00:10:28,470 --> 00:10:29,550
You stare at him.

125
00:10:33,970 --> 00:10:35,050
Are you sad?

126
00:10:35,450 --> 00:10:36,530
No.

127
00:10:36,570 --> 00:10:37,860
Why aren't you sad?

128
00:10:38,030 --> 00:10:39,150
I don't know him.

129
00:10:41,560 --> 00:10:43,690
Gu Yizhong had the same look in his eyes

130
00:10:44,340 --> 00:10:45,770
as you.

131
00:10:45,810 --> 00:10:47,180
How did he do that?

132
00:10:56,250 --> 00:11:00,980
[Against aggression and give me back my country]

